description:
&lt;p&gt;Job Title: Administrator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location/Trust: Barnsley Hospital NHS – Gawber Road, Barnsley S75 2EP&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Department: Medical Records&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band/Pay rate: Band 2 £9.21 per hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: Monday - Friday 3-5 days (flexible) 9am - 5pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Placement Ref: 36292&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Can you bring your administration skills and knowledge to our Medical Records Department?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to be part of a team that works well together, always there to help each other? This location is easily accessible by public transport and has on-site parking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you answered yes, the Barnsley Trust would love to hear from you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a temporary placement opportunity available for an Administrator at Barnsley Hospital NHS Foundation Trust. The administrator will be providing the following support to the medical records team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Significant general clerical experience - admin duties&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Direct telephone contact with clients/staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appointment scheduling&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Comfortable working with staff at all levels&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collate information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The skills required are&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent telephone manner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent IT skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent customer service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competent with Microsoft office suite Word, Excel and Outlook&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong Written/ verbal communication&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Customer care skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prioritising own work loads&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barnsley Hospital NHS Foundation Trust is located on Gawber Road S75 2EP, it is easily accessible via both car and public transport. There is onsite parking (Fees will apply). Barnsley Hospital NHS Foundation Trust has an overall CQC rating of good.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work commitment NHS Professionals (NHSP) can offer you some fantastic benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Pay Rates &lt;/strong&gt;- work this week, get paid next week!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First choice of placements at over 50 NHS Trusts in England &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dedicated consultants&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working options&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Free DBS and free training&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build holiday allowance &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support when you need it – 24/7 365 days&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder pension scheme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are NHS Professionals?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals (NHSP), owned by the Department of Health and Social Care (DHSC), works in partnership with hospital trusts to provide a bank of highly skilled temporary workers who want to work flexibly within the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working through the NHSP bank means Trusts don’t have to rely on expensive agencies. Right now, we have over 130,000 members registered on our bank from various roles, grades and specialities, saving the NHS over &lt;strong&gt;£70 million&lt;/strong&gt; each year. This money is then reinvested back into the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disclaimer &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note, you will be contacted by email throughout the recruitment process, so please check your emails, including your junk/spam regularly. We regret we cannot contact everyone who is not selected for an interview, therefore if you do not hear from us within 21 days after submitting your application, please assume you have not been successful on this occasion&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
